102.1	Red_Scare	Red Scare	The term Red Scare denotes two distinct periods of strong Red Scare Anti-Communism in the United States: the First Red Scare, from 1919 to 1921, and the Second Red Scare, from 1947 to 1957. The First Red Scare was about worker (socialist) revolution and political radicalism. The Second Red Scare was focused on national and foreign communists influencing society, infiltrating the federal government, or both.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Come_unto_me%2C_ye_opprest.jpg/205px-Come_unto_me%2C_ye_opprest.jpg
